Seven.

116
00:07:18.620 --> 00:07:21.623
Someone made the decision
to hunt over by Brant Lake.


117
00:07:21.658 --> 00:07:22.590
Who made that decision?

118
00:07:22.624 --> 00:07:24.454
I did.

119
00:07:24.488 --> 00:07:27.215
SID: I messaged
that we had state
land there.


120
00:07:27.249 --> 00:07:30.494
We kind of agreed to hunt it.
The roads of Lily Pond.


121
00:07:42.989 --> 00:07:45.060
I mean, we go up that road,
straight to the lake


122
00:07:45.095 --> 00:07:47.718
and we parked
right at the lake.


123
00:07:47.753 --> 00:07:51.722
And the old guys
literally walked down that road

124
00:07:51.757 --> 00:07:53.241
in hundred yard increments.

125
00:07:58.073 --> 00:08:02.837
We walked in 30, 40 yards
at the most and sat down.


126
00:08:11.086 --> 00:08:12.847
Al was the first watcher.

127
00:08:12.881 --> 00:08:14.262
I was the second.

128
00:08:14.952 --> 00:08:17.265
Joe Capacelli, and then Tom.

129
00:08:18.197 --> 00:08:19.888
So, Tom was furthest
from the lake?


130
00:08:19.923 --> 00:08:21.890
He was the furthest one.

131
00:08:21.925 --> 00:08:24.065
We followed the trail along
the lake,


132
00:08:24.099 --> 00:08:26.170
come up that snowmobile trail,

133
00:08:26.205 --> 00:08:28.345
hopped into the woods,
and swung up to him.


134
00:08:28.379 --> 00:08:31.037
A slow
hunt-and-drive type thing.


135
00:08:32.487 --> 00:08:35.455
BEVERLY: The young boys said
to the old men,


136
00:08:35.490 --> 00:08:37.250
"You four sit here,

137
00:08:37.285 --> 00:08:40.875
and if we see any deer,
we'll push them towards you."


138
00:08:40.909 --> 00:08:44.603
And if Tom was a watcher,
Tom would not have moved.


139
00:08:44.637 --> 00:08:46.708
I know that for a fact.

140
00:08:46.743 --> 00:08:48.917
He was a watcher,
that's where he was.


141
00:09:03.138 --> 00:09:05.727
-DAVID: Did you see any deer?
-SID: None at all.


142
00:09:05.762 --> 00:09:08.592
-No.
-Did you hear anything?


143
00:09:08.627 --> 00:09:13.114
I heard a strange noise
in the woods, but I don't know
what it was.


144
00:09:13.148 --> 00:09:16.945
Just a different noise from what
I usually hear, you know?


145
00:09:16.980 --> 00:09:18.188
DAVID: Like what?

146
00:09:19.914 --> 00:09:22.054
It'd be hard
to explain because...


147
00:09:22.088 --> 00:09:23.400
But it was different.

148
00:09:23.434 --> 00:09:26.437
Something different that I never
heard before in the woods.


149
00:09:28.163 --> 00:09:30.476
I just can't say what it was,
you know?


150
00:09:30.510 --> 00:09:33.617
How long in duration was it?
Was it two or three seconds?


151
00:09:33.652 --> 00:09:35.585
No, it's just...

152
00:09:35.619 --> 00:09:36.931
Whatever it is, you know?

153
00:09:38.277 --> 00:09:40.244
DAVID: How far away was it?

154
00:09:40.279 --> 00:09:44.317
SID: I'd say it was
probably 150 yards, something like that.

155
00:09:44.352 --> 00:09:46.354
DAVID: Was it toward Tom,
or away from Tom?


156
00:09:46.388 --> 00:09:49.909
SID: This was up
towards the hill.
The top of the hill. Yeah.


157
00:09:49.944 --> 00:09:51.531
DAVID: Did you tell
the cops this?


158
00:09:51.566 --> 00:09:52.463
Yeah, I told them that.

159
00:09:52.498 --> 00:09:55.225
But they just passed it off,
you know?


160
00:09:58.780 --> 00:10:01.749
DAVID: The report said that
your dad was carrying
a walkie-talkie?


161
00:10:01.783 --> 00:10:03.613
-ROB: Yeah.
-DAVID: Who else had one?


162
00:10:03.647 --> 00:10:04.683
We all did.

163
00:10:04.717 --> 00:10:06.823
-All on the same channel?
-Yup.


164
00:10:06.857 --> 00:10:08.514
-Anybody ever hear anything?
-No.


165
00:10:10.309 --> 00:10:11.655
DAVID: Did your dad know
how to use it?


166
00:10:11.690 --> 00:10:12.622
ROB: Yep.

167
00:10:24.599 --> 00:10:26.946
