1433
01:24:43.950 --> 01:24:46.091
JAN: Hunting in Ohio
is awesome.


1434
01:24:46.125 --> 01:24:49.542
We have some great, big
trophy deer in Ohio


1435
01:24:49.577 --> 01:24:50.750
and we happen to have

1436
01:24:50.785 --> 01:24:53.236
some of the biggest right
here on our own property.

1437
01:25:16.845 --> 01:25:18.778
It was the most
beautiful night to deer hunt.

1438
01:25:18.813 --> 01:25:20.125
It was the second day
of season.


1439
01:25:20.159 --> 01:25:23.266
I wanted to get into
the woods to hunt.


1440
01:25:23.300 --> 01:25:24.784
I was very excited about it.

1441
01:25:29.513 --> 01:25:32.689
There was band,
over at the high school.


1442
01:25:34.829 --> 01:25:37.072
By the time I got to my deer
stand, I could hear 'em.


1443
01:25:40.800 --> 01:25:41.974
I was all settled in.

1444
01:25:42.008 --> 01:25:43.631
Didn't see nothing coming
down the pass.


1445
01:25:43.665 --> 01:25:46.668
Trails of birds,
crickets, everything was
normal wood sounds.


1446
01:25:48.532 --> 01:25:49.947
When you're hunting,

1447
01:25:49.982 --> 01:25:52.467
you have two
of your keenest senses.


1448
01:25:52.502 --> 01:25:54.159
It's your hearing
and your eyesight.


1449
01:25:58.232 --> 01:26:01.856
All of a sudden, the woods
went to this dead quiet.


1450
01:26:05.031 --> 01:26:07.551
If I had dropped a pin,
I know that deer would stand.


1451
01:26:09.691 --> 01:26:10.865
They had cut off.

1452
01:26:10.899 --> 01:26:13.833
No birds, no crickets,
no nothing.


1453
01:26:15.318 --> 01:26:16.629
With the sun still up,

1454
01:26:16.664 --> 01:26:18.528
we were not calling for
bad weather that night.


1455
01:26:18.562 --> 01:26:19.943
It was a great night to hunt.

1456
01:26:22.532 --> 01:26:25.293
All of a sudden,
I thought I had
a mote in my eye.


1457
01:26:25.328 --> 01:26:27.709
I even took my finger
and rubbed my eye, like,


1458
01:26:27.744 --> 01:26:29.332
when you get that fogginess
over your eye,


1459
01:26:29.366 --> 01:26:30.850
like, it's just...

1460
01:26:30.885 --> 01:26:32.507
I look and I'm thinking,

1461
01:26:32.542 --> 01:26:34.578
"What is this thing
in the trees?"


1462
01:26:36.097 --> 01:26:39.549
It looked like a large piece
of Saran Wrap.


1463
01:26:39.583 --> 01:26:40.929
It's the only way
I can describe it.


1464
01:26:40.964 --> 01:26:42.345
But this thing was very wide.

1465
01:26:42.379 --> 01:26:46.349
'Cause I'm up 14 foot
and it hung quite a ways down


1466
01:26:46.383 --> 01:26:47.798
and I'm thinking...

1467
01:26:48.385 --> 01:26:49.593
"What is this thing?"

1468
01:26:50.698 --> 01:26:52.872
It didn't really scare me
at that time,


1469
01:26:52.907 --> 01:26:54.943
until it moved and formed

1470
01:26:54.978 --> 01:26:57.705
the arm that reached over
to the other tree.


1471
01:26:57.739 --> 01:27:00.535
It reached over
about 12 to 14 foot.


1472
01:27:00.570 --> 01:27:04.229
And then, it all, like
a blob, sucked into it.

1473
01:27:04.263 --> 01:27:05.920
And it went to
a whole other tree.


1474
01:27:07.301 --> 01:27:09.268
I had this very important
feeling, like,


1475
01:27:09.303 --> 01:27:11.270
something ain't right here.

1476
01:27:12.789 --> 01:27:14.722
Normally at that time, I would
have probably got down


1477
01:27:14.756 --> 01:27:16.413
and stopped hunting,

1478
01:27:16.448 --> 01:27:17.794
but for some reason, I didn't.

1479
01:27:18.967 --> 01:27:20.969
DAVID: So, as you're sitting
in your blind,


1480
01:27:21.004 --> 01:27:22.730
and you're looking across,

1481
01:27:22.764 --> 01:27:25.733
where did the blob come from?

1482
01:27:25.767 --> 01:27:29.702
I have no idea.
It just appeared
in the one tree.


1483
01:27:29.737 --> 01:27:31.773
As it was moving
through the woods,


1484
01:27:31.808 --> 01:27:33.982
it went from tree
to tree to tree


1485
01:27:34.017 --> 01:27:35.984
and then it just disappeared.

1486
01:27:36.640 --> 01:27:38.642
It didn't continue on.

1487
01:27:38.677 --> 01:27:40.265
So, where it went I don't know,

1488
01:27:40.299 --> 01:27:43.164
but it just... Right before my
eyes, just vanished.


1489
01:27:45.200 --> 01:27:48.445
And I don't remember
taking the picture,


1490
01:27:48.480 --> 01:27:52.587
but being married to
who I'm married to,
Dr. Bruce Maccabee,


1491
01:27:52.622 --> 01:27:56.108
he always said, "If you see
anything weird, get a picture."


1492
01:27:59.629 --> 01:28:05.428
I don't recall actually when
either that the sounds had returned.

1493
01:28:05.462 --> 01:28:07.844
It's just like I don't remember.

1494
01:28:10.467 --> 01:28:11.917
That's not me to this day.

1495
01:28:11.951 --> 01:28:13.746
Normally, I would probably
crawl down,


1496
01:28:13.781 --> 01:28:15.438
come around the house and say,

1497
01:28:15.472 --> 01:28:17.336
"You ain't going to believe
what's back there
in the woods."


1498
01:28:17.371 --> 01:28:19.890
DAVID: How much longer
do you think
you stayed in the stand?


1499
01:28:21.340 --> 01:28:24.999
About half hour till sundown.
It was time to come out.


1500
01:28:29.659 --> 01:28:31.454
The strange part about this is,

1501
01:28:31.488 --> 01:28:32.869
Jan goes off to hunt,

1502
01:28:34.008 --> 01:28:36.631
we have guests show up,
we're having dinner.


1503
01:28:36.666 --> 01:28:38.012
She comes back from the hunt

1504
01:28:38.046 --> 01:28:40.325
and says nothing about what
happened. It was strange.


1505
01:28:41.705 --> 01:28:44.121
The guests are
about ready to leave.


1506
01:28:44.156 --> 01:28:47.159
Later on, Matthew sends me
an e-mail.


1507
01:28:47.193 --> 01:28:49.161
BRUCE: There was sighting
by a number of students


1508
01:28:49.195 --> 01:28:51.819
and faculty in the high school
band practice,


1509
01:28:51.853 --> 01:28:53.338
just before dark.

1510
01:28:53.924 --> 01:28:55.340
I'm like, "Holy crap.

1511
01:28:55.374 --> 01:28:57.928
Maybe it has something to do
with what I saw in the woods."


1512
01:28:58.653 --> 01:28:59.861
And Bruce goes, "What?"

1513
01:29:00.241 --> 01:29:01.656
And I said,

1514
01:29:01.691 --> 01:29:05.557
"I forgot to tell you what
happened in those woods
to me tonight."


1515
01:29:05.591 --> 01:29:07.628
And I'm reading
this from Matthew


1516
01:29:07.662 --> 01:29:10.009
and then I start
getting goosebumps.


1517
01:29:10.044 --> 01:29:11.839
He said
this light appeared above


1518
01:29:11.873 --> 01:29:15.049
like big stadium lights
in the football field.


1519
01:29:15.083 --> 01:29:16.809
Had Matthew
not sent that e-mail,


1520
01:29:16.844 --> 01:29:20.261
I'm not sure if I would have
remembered even that night to
say anything.


1521
01:29:22.401 --> 01:29:24.023
DAVID: How many kids
were on the field?


1522
01:29:24.058 --> 01:29:26.405
MATTHEW: At least 30.
Thirty to forty
I would say.


1523
01:29:26.440 --> 01:29:27.855
DAVID: And was that
the high school band?


1524
01:29:27.889 --> 01:29:29.581
MATTHEW: Yes.

1525
01:29:29.615 --> 01:29:31.859
DAVID: And so, this was
just before you guys went
back to school?


1526
01:29:31.893 --> 01:29:33.999
MATTHEW: Yes, band camp.

1527
01:29:34.033 --> 01:29:35.828
-MATTHEW: Late August.
-DAVID: Late August?


1528
01:29:35.863 --> 01:29:38.037
So, what time at night
do you think that was?


1529
01:29:38.900 --> 01:29:40.212
Between six and seven.

1530
01:29:40.246 --> 01:29:43.008
We were rehearsing
normally out here


1531
01:29:43.042 --> 01:29:45.010
about six or seven o'clock,

1532
01:29:45.044 --> 01:29:47.288
doing our normal routine.

1533
01:29:47.322 --> 01:29:49.670
When, all of a sudden, there was
this bright light in the sky


1534
01:29:49.704 --> 01:29:51.396
that just came out of nowhere.

1535
01:29:53.052 --> 01:29:55.400
And we all just kind of
stopped and looked at it as one.

1536
01:29:56.539 --> 01:29:58.126
DAVID: Where was the light?

1537
01:29:58.161 --> 01:30:01.613
So, the light was anywhere...

1538
01:30:01.647 --> 01:30:03.062
It was above
the treeline for sure,


1539
01:30:03.097 --> 01:30:05.927
just kind of hovering
in the skyline.


1540
01:30:06.928 --> 01:30:08.792
Close enough for it
to catch your attention.


1541
01:30:10.415 --> 01:30:11.795
Like, it shouldn't have been
there, I guess.


1542
01:30:11.830 --> 01:30:13.452
If it was some man made thing,

1543
01:30:13.487 --> 01:30:14.936
it was too low to be there.

1544
01:30:16.351 --> 01:30:19.251
Okay, what was the weather
like that night?


1545
01:30:19.285 --> 01:30:20.735
Clear and hot.

1546
01:30:20.770 --> 01:30:22.150
Typical August Ohio weather.

1547
01:30:22.185 --> 01:30:24.532
DAVID: Okay,
what color was it?


1548
01:30:24.567 --> 01:30:25.809
MATTHEW: Candle orange.

1549
01:30:25.844 --> 01:30:27.052
As far as I can tell,

1550
01:30:27.086 --> 01:30:28.916
the thing had
no definable edges to it.


1551
01:30:28.950 --> 01:30:30.089
There were no,
like, dimensions.


1552
01:30:30.124 --> 01:30:32.747
It was just kind of waxing
and waning


1553
01:30:32.782 --> 01:30:34.473
till it zapped out.

1554
01:30:34.508 --> 01:30:36.717
You know, our band director,
he never stops for anything.


1555
01:30:36.751 --> 01:30:39.478
He stopped and turned around
and looked at this and goes,


1556
01:30:39.513 --> 01:30:41.273
"What the hell was that?"

1557
01:30:41.307 --> 01:30:44.276
Before I had time to even
think of what I was
seeing, it was gone.


1558
01:30:44.310 --> 01:30:46.278
And then it was just kind of
an imprint in your mind,


1559
01:30:46.312 --> 01:30:47.969
like I've seen
something strange.


1560
01:30:51.456 --> 01:30:55.494
DAVID: So, in your gut,
are the two issues related?


1561
01:30:55.529 --> 01:30:58.117
I often wonder now.

1562
01:30:58.152 --> 01:31:00.292
All I can say is it happened
within the same time frame


1563
01:31:00.326 --> 01:31:03.122
basically as
my experience here.


1564
01:31:03.157 --> 01:31:06.056
About half a mile over there,
